    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.6.0 commit e65b724\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 8.2.3582\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman -S neovim\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n1. set terminal font large enough (in my example it's 64px per character)\r\n2. launch neovim\r\n3. set colorscheme which has a background (in my example, I use the built in colorscheme blue)\r\n4. resize terminal window to make it not align to character size. (for example, 1279 x 767, which is (64 x 19 + 63) x (64 x 11 + 63) that is not suitable to place characters with 20 per row and 12 per column.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nvim background color fill all the terminal.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe black background which is circled by red box is not expected.\r\n![border](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24190403/145232638-b0ad13e3-bbb3-4e49-b42f-88e25b9454b9.png)\r\n![border2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24190403/145232747-ccde76e1-eea6-4ee9-80ca-6a76ed2e53a6.png)\r\n\r\n",
