            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "There's a quick solution; some terminals can change padding inside them; like CSS objects; as an example I'm using wezterm but it should also works on Alacritty\r\n\r\nUsing wezterm documentation\r\n```\r\n  -- Window\r\n  window_padding = {\r\n    bottom = 0,\r\n    right = 0,\r\n    left = 0,\r\n    top = 0,\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://wezfurlong.org/wezterm/config/lua/config/window_padding.html\r\n  \r\nUsing Kitty; setting padding to a 1 or 0 it should be less anoying\r\n`window_padding_width 0`\r\nhttps://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/conf/?highlight=padding#opt-kitty.window_padding_width\r\n  \r\nUsing Alacritty, it should also works\r\n```\r\nwindow:\r\n  padding:\r\n   x: 0\r\n   y: 0\r\n\r\n```\r\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/67250738/how-to-add-padding-to-my-alacritty-terminal-in-awesomewm",
