            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Is this something that needs to be \"fixed\" in Neovim core at all?\r\n\r\nIf `Normal` sets a background color, the TUI could decide by to fill the terminal margins with that color, by default (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/16592). But then we may get requests to _opt-out_ of that behavior, and I agree that a new option for this seems overwrought.\r\n\r\n# Status\r\n\r\nTo close this issue, let's just add a note at `:help 'background'` that mentions a `chansend()` (or related) code needed to send the \"fill margins\" terminal sequence.",
            "created_at": "2024-02-18T16:14:28Z",
